kubectl (CLI tool to control the cluster)
│
├── Cluster (the whole Kubernetes environment)
│   │
│   ├── Nodes (machines that run workloads)
│   │   │
│   │   ├── Pods (smallest deployable unit, containers run here)
│   │   │   │
│   │   │   ├── awx-web pod (serves the AWX UI in browser)
│   │   │   ├── awx-task pod (executes jobs, playbooks, background tasks)
│   │   │   ├── awx-postgres pod (database for AWX data)
│   │   │   └── awx-migration pod (one-time DB schema updates)
│   │   │
│   │   └── Other system pods (DNS, metrics, etc.)
│   │
│   ├── Deployments (controllers that ensure pods stay running)
│   │   └── Manage replicas of awx-web, awx-task, etc.
│   │
│   ├── Services (stable network endpoints to reach pods)
│   │   ├── ClusterIP (internal only)
│   │   ├── NodePort (exposes AWX on node’s IP + port)
│   │   └── Ingress (optional, clean hostname access like awx.local)
│   │
│   └── Namespace (logical grouping of resources, e.g., "awx")
│
├── AWX Operator (special controller that automates AWX lifecycle)
│   │
│   ├── Custom Resource (AWX CR, e.g., awx-deploy.yaml)
│   │   └── Defines desired state: replicas, service type, secrets
│   │
│   └── Reconciliation loop (ensures pods/services match CR spec)
│
└── Secrets (store sensitive data)
    └── awx-admin-password (used to log into AWX UI)
